    • Constructor Detail

      • Orchestrator

        public Orchestrator(ModelProvider modelProvider,
                    ModelSchemaRegistry modelSchemaRegistry,
                    LocalStorageAdapter localStorageAdapter,
                    AppSync appSync,
                    DataStoreConfigurationProvider dataStoreConfigurationProvider,
                    <any> targetState)
        Constructs a new Orchestrator. The Orchestrator will synchronize data between the AppSync and the LocalStorageAdapter.
        Parameters:
        modelProvider - A provider of the models to be synchronized
        modelSchemaRegistry - A registry of model schema
        localStorageAdapter - used to durably store offline changes until they can be written to the network
        appSync - An AppSync Endpoint
        dataStoreConfigurationProvider - A DataStoreConfigurationProvider; Note that the provider-style interface is needed because at the time this constructor is called from the AWSDataStorePlugin's constructor, the plugin is not fully configured yet. The reference to the variable returned by the provider only get set after the plugin's AWSDataStorePlugin.configure(JSONObject, Context) is invoked by Amplify.
        targetState - The desired state of operation - online, or offline

        Start the orchestrator.

        A completable which emits success when the orchestrator has transitioned to LOCAL_ONLY (synchronously) and started (asynchronously) the transition to SYNC_VIA_API, if an API is available.
